         <div xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143"><!-- p5l3-r8 -->
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Hd1e108">Rubrica 8</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De miseria et miseris</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="11"/>¶ De minseria et minseris. Rubrica. 8.
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e119">
               <lb ed="#V" n="12"/>hysto. c. 5. <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e123">Deus ponit hui
        <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>Tobles in sublime: et mentes
        <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>erigit sospitate.</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e131"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e133"> 36. c. Quidam ami
        <lb ed="#V" n="15" break="no"/>cus Iob noie elium in consolatione. Iob dixit
        <lb ed="#V" n="16"/>ei: Caue ne declines ad inditatem. Hanc enim
        <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>cepisti sequi post minseriam.
        <lb ed="#V" n="18"/>Salomon in prouerbiis. c. 19. Homo in
        <lb ed="#V" n="19" break="no"/>digens minsericors est. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e148">
               <lb ed="#V" n="20"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e152">¶ Salustius in iugurtino: Expertus sum pa
        <lb ed="#V" n="21" break="no"/>rum fidei minseris esse. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e158">
               <lb ed="#V" n="22"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e162">¶ Tullius padoxorum. dist. 2. Ut improbo et stul
        <lb ed="#V" n="23" break="no"/>to et ierti nemini bene esse potest: Sic bonus vir
        <lb ed="#V" n="24"/>et fortis et sapiens miser esse non potest. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e170">
               <lb ed="#V" n="25"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e174">¶ Quidius de ponto. l. 2. e. 7. Res timida est
        <lb ed="#V" n="26"/>omnis miser. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e180"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e182"> Libro. 4. et fi. e. 4
        <lb ed="#V" n="27"/>Nil adeo fortuna grauis miserabile fecit:
        <lb ed="#V" n="28"/>Ut muniant nulla gaudia per te malum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e190">
               <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e194">/ Epistola. 12
        <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>Crede mihi misos prudentia summa reliquit.
        <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>Et sensus cum re consiliumque fugit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e202">
               <lb ed="#V" n="32"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e206">/ Idem de nuce.
        <lb ed="#V" n="33"/>Qe miserum est odium dannis accedere nostris. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e213">
               <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e217">¶ Quintilianus declam. i. declam. Semper si
        <lb ed="#V" n="35" break="no"/>bi custodiunt minseri.: ne esse miserabiles desi
        <lb ed="#V" n="36" break="no"/>nant. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e225"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e227"> 13 declam. Leuior est calamitas cui
        <lb ed="#V" n="37"/>blanditur aliquid de voluptate letitia. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e233">
               <lb ed="#V" n="38"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e237">¶ Seneca tragediarum in thieste. c. 11.
        <lb ed="#V" n="39"/>Proprium hc miseros sequitur vicium.
        <lb ed="#V" n="40"/>Nunquam rebus crede letis.
        <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>Redere felix fortuna licet.
        <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>Tamen afflictos gaudere piget.
        <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>Flendi minseris dira cupido est. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e251">
               <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e255">/ In troa. c. 12. et penul.
        <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>Nemo se credit miserum: sit licet. <!--321.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>Tolle felices. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e267">
               <lb ed="#V" n="47"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e271">/ Idem epistolarum ad lucillum. el. 9. e. i.
        <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>Nemo nisi vicio miser est. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e277">
               <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e281">/ Idem declam. l. 8 causa. i. Fortuna quos mise
        <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>ros facit etiam superstitiosos facit. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e288">
               <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e292">¶ Lucanus vel 3. Seruat multos fortuma nocem
        <lb ed="#V" n="52"/>tes. Et tantum minseris irasci numina possunt. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e298">
               <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e302">¶ Statius thebayd. lib. 11. Hic minseris fu
        <lb ed="#V" n="54" break="no"/>ror est: astare periculo. Nec librare metus: et tu
        <lb ed="#V" n="55"/>ta odisse. Quid causus iuuat ostentare pudentes </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e310">
               <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e314">/ Li. 12Amant misi lamenta: malisque fruuntur. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e318">
               <lb ed="#V" n="57"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e322">¶ Fulgentius vel. i. fab. i. Sola est medicina
        <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>minseriarum obliuio. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e328">
               <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e332">¶ Boetius de consolatione. l. i. c. 8. Hic etiam ve
        <lb ed="#V" n="60"/>stris cumulis malis accedit: quod existimatio
        <lb ed="#V" n="61"/>istolimorum non rerum merita: sed fortue spectat euen
        <lb ed="#V" n="62" break="no"/>tum. eaque tantum iudicat esse prouisa qui felicitas commen
        <lb ed="#V" n="63"/>dauerint. Quo fit vt existiatio bona prima omni
        <lb ed="#V" n="64" break="no"/>um deserat ifelices. hoc tantum dixerim vltimam
        <lb ed="#V" n="65"/>esse aduerse fortune sarcinam: quod dum mise
        <lb ed="#V" n="66" break="no"/>ris aliquod crimen affigitur que proferuntur
        <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>meruisse redduntur. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e353">
               <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e357">¶ Cassiodorus epistolarum vel. 5. e. 29 Necesse est
        <lb ed="#V" n="69"/>vt amplius permoueat visa quam audita calami
        <lb ed="#V" n="70"/>tas. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e366"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e368"> 36. e. Non est ignauie culpa quam excusat
        <lb ed="#V" n="71"/>miseranda calamitas. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e374"> /
      <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e376"> Li. 10. e. i. Deus consue
        <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>uit casus asperos in prospera commutare. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e382">
               <lb ed="#V" n="73"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e386">¶ Auctor scilicet qui dicitur pamphylus. c. 18. Parua
        <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>nocent misis: misos mala multa sequuntur.
        <lb ed="#V" n="75"/>Spesque laborque suus remanent in dubio. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e394">
               <lb ed="#V" n="76"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e398">¶ Gualterius de castellione vel. 6. Sors mise
        <lb ed="#V" n="77"/>ri querula est. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e404">
               <lb ed="#V" n="78"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e408">¶ Iacobus beneuentanus. c. 52. Ludibrium
        <lb ed="#V" n="79"/>populo fit miser omnis homo. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e414">
               <lb ed="#V" n="80"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e418">¶ Prouerb. metritur. extraoro vel vag. Solati
        <lb ed="#V" n="81" break="no"/>um est minseris socios habere penarum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-d1e425">
               <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e08143-Qd1e429">¶ Prouerb. vul. Ai cham magri vale mosche. </quote>
            </p>
         </div>
